225 grams British Pork and Oregano Sausage Meat
40 grams Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese
100 grams Baby Spinach
180 grams Spaghetti
1 carton(s) Finely Chopped Tomatoes with Onion and Garlic
10 grams Chicken Stock Paste
30 grams Tomato Puree
1 pinch Chilli Flakes
½ tsp Sugar

Boil a full kettle.
Heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on medium-high heat.
Once hot, fry the sausage meat, 5-6 mins.
Break it up as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a saucepan with 1/4 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the spaghetti, 8 mins.

Next, add the chopped tomatoes, chicken stock paste, sugar (see pantry), chilli flakes and tomato puree to the sausage meat.
Stir together. Simmer, 5-6 mins.
Add the spinach in handfuls so it's piping hot, 1-2 mins.

Once cooked, add the spaghetti to the sauce.
Stir in half the hard Italian style cheese. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.
Serve the pasta in bowls sprinkled with the remaining cheese.
Enjoy!